{{Chinese |pic=Chengdu panda breeding.jpg |piccap=The facility entrance |picsize=275px |order=st
|s=成都大熊猫繁育研究基地 |t=成都大熊貓繁育研究基地 |p=Chéngdū Dàxióngmāo fányù Yánjiū Jīdì }}
'''Chengdu Research Base of Giant Panda Breeding''', or simply '''Chengdu Panda Base''', is a non-profit research and breeding facility for [[giant panda]]s and other rare animals. It is located in [[Chengdu]], [[Sichuan]], [[China]]. [[File:Chengdu Research Base Eingang.jpg|thumb|Entrance of the Chengdu Research Base of Giant Panda Breeding]] [[File:Chengdu Research Base of Giant Panda Breeding Eingangsschild.jpg|thumb]] [[File:1 panda trio sichuan china 2011.jpg|thumb]] [[File:Giant Panda at Chengdu Panda Base.jpg|thumb|A [[giant panda]] at Chengdu Panda Base]]
Chengdu Panda Base was founded in 1987. It started with 6 giant pandas that were rescued from the wild. By 2008, it had 124 panda births, and the captive panda population has grown to 83.<ref name=about>{{cite web|title=About Chengdu Panda Base|url=http://www.panda.org.cn/english/about/about/2013-09-11/2416.html}}</ref>
Its stated goal is to "be a world-class research facility, conservation education center, and international educational tourism destination."<ref name=about/>
==Partnerships== Chengdu Panda Base has partnered with many organizations in improving ways to conserve giant pandas. For example, its partnership with [[Zoo Atlanta]] helped the zoo secure the loan of 2 giant pandas.<ref name=atlanta>{{cite web|title=Zoo Atlanta's Conservation Education Initiative in China|url=http://www.zooatlanta.org/conservation_education.htm|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080317023904/http://www.zooatlanta.org/conservation_education.htm|archivedate=2008-03-17|df=}}</ref> To date, these 2 giant pandas, [[Yang Yang (Atlanta giant panda)|Yang Yang]] and [[Lun Lun]], have produced five off-spring: [[Mei Lan]] in 2006, [[Xi Lan]] in 2008, Po born on November 3, 2010 and Mei Lun and Mei Huan in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=New Giant Panda cub born at Zoo Atlanta|url=http://www.zooatlanta.com/zoo_news_panda_birth_2008.htm|publisher=Zoo Atlanta}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Zoo Atlanta's Giant Panda Cub Is Named Xi Lan|url=http://www.zooatlanta.com/zoo_news_panda_xilan_name.htm|publisher=Zoo Atlanta|date=December 8, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=2010's only US giant panda cub born in Atlanta zoo|url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/US/11/03/georgia.panda.cub/index.html?hpt=T2|publisher=CNN|date=2010-11-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Zoo Atlanta and Dreamworks Animation Announce Panda Cub’s New Name|url=http://www.zooatlanta.org/home/article_content/pandacub_100day_po|publisher=Zoo Atlanta|date=February 15, 2011|access-date=2011-03-28|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6GpWxxUN7?url=http://www.zooatlanta.org/home/article_content/pandacub_100day_po#|archive-date=2013-05-23|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
Other research partners include:<ref name=partners>{{cite web|title=Research partners|url=http://www.panda.org.cn/english/about/cooperation/2013-09-12/2418.html}}</ref> *Adventure World in [[Shirahama, Wakayama]], [[Japan]] *East Bay Zoological Society, [[Oakland, California]], United States *[[University of Liverpool]], [[England|England, UK]] *[[National Institute of Health]]/National Cancer Institution, United States *[[National Zoological Park (United States)|National Zoological Park]], [[Washington, D.C.]], United States *[[Nihon University|Nihon University, Tokyo, Japan]] *North of England Zoological Society, England, UK *The Oakland China Wildlife Preservation Foundation, California, United States *[[San Diego Zoo]], California, United States *University of Japan *[[Edinburgh Zoo]], [[Scotland]], UK *[[Calgary Zoo]], [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]], [[Canada]]
On April 11, 2013 Chengdu Research Base of Giant Panda Breeding and [[China Network Television|CNTV]] reached an agreement on the establishment of iPanda.com after an official signing ceremony, and they immediately started preparing for the test launch (which was estimated in June, 2013).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.panda.org.cn/china/news/news/2013-04-12/997.html|title=央视网络 "熊猫频道"合作签字仪式在北京举行 - 成都大熊猫繁育研究基地|website=www.panda.org.cn|access-date=2016-10-15}}</ref>
