An '''''ostiole''''' is a small hole or opening through which [[algae]]<ref>Fletcher, R.L. 1987. ''Seaweeds of the British Isles. Volume 3 Fucophyceae (Phaeophyceae) Part 1'' p.304 British Museum (Natural History) {{ISBN|0-565-00992-3}}</ref> or [[fungi]] release their mature [[spore]]s. The term is also used in [[higher plant]]s, for example to denote the opening of the involuted [[ficus|fig]] inflorescence through which [[fig wasp]]s enter to [[Pollination|pollinate]] and breed.

